  "prompt": "Can peppermint oil keep mice away?",
  "response": "Yes, peppermint oil is often used as a natural deterrent to keep mice away. The strong scent of peppermint is believed to be unpleasant for mice, making it a potential repellent. To use peppermint oil for this purpose, you can place cotton balls soaked in peppermint oil in areas where you've noticed mouse activity or in potential entry points, such as cracks and crevices.\n\nHowever, while peppermint oil may help reduce the likelihood of mice entering an area, it is not a guaranteed solution. If you have a significant mouse problem, it may be best to combine the use of peppermint oil with other pest control methods, such as sealing entry points, maintaining cleanliness, and, if necessary, employing traps or professional pest control services.",
